songs.title: Another Love

description.plain:
In an interview, Tom Odell explains:

“Another Love” is a confusing one; it’s not a traditional love song. The song, for me, is about trying—really trying with all your heart—to be with someone else and you want to be with someone else. The song was written talking to this girl that I really wanted to be with, and I was trying to work out why I couldn’t be with her. And it’s funny, people sometimes listen to it as [though] I’m more talking about the last romance.

songs.title: Heal

description.plain:
“Heal” captures the narrator’s vulnerability in wanting reassurance within a relationship. It appears in the 2014 movie If I Stay. The song plays during the moment in which the main character decides if they want to keep on living.

It appears on Tom Odell’s album Long Way Down.

songs.title: Can’t Pretend

description.plain:
“Can’t Pretend” is the first single from Tom Odell’s debut album, Long Way Down.

The song was used in the trailer “Desert” of the second season of The Newsroom, as well as The Blacklist episode “Milton Bobbit”, Crisis episode “Found” and The 100 episode “Earth Skills”.
